### 


### 📱 SMS NOTIFICATIONS API TESTS


### Base endpoint: /api/sms-notif


### 


### This file contains tests for SMS notification endpoints using Telnyx.


### Update the variables below and run requests with :Rest run


### 


### Authentication required:


### - x-api-key: Global API key


### 


### Note: Phone numbers must be in E.164 format (+[country code][number])


### Example: +14155552671 (US), +442071838750 (UK), +4512345678 (Denmark)


### 


### ============================================


### ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES


### ============================================


### Variables are loaded from tests/.http-client.env.json


### Copy tests/.http-client.env.json.example to tests/.http-client.env.json


### and fill in your values. See tests/README.md for setup instructions.


### ============================================


### ============================================


### POST - Send SMS Notification


### ============================================


### send-sms-single-recipient-with-sender

# Expected: 200 OK
# Sends SMS to single recipient with custom sender name
# Handler: backend/app/api/sms-notif/handler/telnyx.ts:17

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "senderName": "{{smsSender}}",
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}"
}


### send-sms-single-recipient-without-sender

# Expected: 200 OK
# Sends SMS without custom sender name (uses Telnyx default phone number if configured)

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}"
}


### send-sms-multiple-recipients

# Expected: 200 OK
# Sends SMS to multiple recipients (array format)
# Returns success/failure status for each recipient

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "to": [
    "{{phoneNumber}}",
    "{{phone2}}",
    "{{phone3}}"
  ]
}


### send-sms-multiple-recipients-with-sender

# Expected: 200 OK
# Sends SMS to multiple recipients with custom sender

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "senderName": "{{smsSender}}",
  "to": [
    "{{phoneNumber}}",
    "{{phone2}}",
    "{{phone3}}",
    "{{phone4}}"
  ]
}


### send-sms-short-message

# Expected: 200 OK
# Tests: Very short message content

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{shortMessage}}",
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}"
}


### send-sms-long-message

# Expected: 200 OK (or may be split into multiple SMS)
# Tests: Long message content (may exceed single SMS limit)

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{longMessage}}",
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}"
}


### send-sms-invalid-phone-format

# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Phone number not in E.164 format

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "to": "{{invalidPhone}}"
}


### send-sms-invalid-phone-string

# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Invalid phone number (non-numeric)

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "to": "{{invalidPhone2}}"
}


### send-sms-missing-body

# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Missing required body field

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}"
}


### send-sms-empty-body

# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Empty message body

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{emptyMessage}}",
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}"
}


### send-sms-missing-recipient

# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Missing required to field

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}"
}


### send-sms-empty-recipients-array

# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Empty array for recipients

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "to": []
}


### send-sms-mixed-valid-invalid-recipients

# Expected: 200 OK (partial success)
# Tests: Some valid recipients, some invalid
# Should return success for valid, failure for invalid

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "to": [
    "{{phoneNumber}}",
    "{{invalidPhone}}",
    "{{phone2}}"
  ]
}


### send-sms-empty-request

# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Completely empty request body

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}


### send-sms-null-sender

# Expected: 200 OK
# Tests: Explicitly null sender name (should use default phone number if TELNYX_PHONE_NUMBER is configured)

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "senderName": null,
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}"
}


### send-sms-empty-sender

# Expected: 200 OK
# Tests: Empty string sender name (should use default phone number if TELNYX_PHONE_NUMBER is configured)

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif HTTP/1.1
X-Api-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "senderName": "",
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}"
}
